 • Editor’s note: Livestream above courtesy DStv 403. You can also watch it on DStv Now. JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng MEC for Human Settlements, Urban Planning and COGTA, Lebogang Maile, met with mayors from all municipalities to discuss the electricity crisis in the province. Maile and his delegation held a bilateral meeting with Eskom CEO, André de Ruyter. READ: Emfuleni property attached over Eskom debt Electricity challenges, as well as debts owed to Eskom, are set to be discussed. Last week, the sheriff of the court seized property belonging to Emfuleni Municipality. Eskom says the total debt owed by the municipality was over R2-billion.